#ASH22 

@ASH_hematology has 2 hours to release the ASH Education book before I board my plane to New Orleans.

Anyone in New Orleans tonight want to get a beer and talk hematology DM me. https://t.co/IoYWmTnGp6

@MichaelJSlade @CyclingDoctor @LabFehniger @DiPersioLab @ManniMD1 @DavidSteensma @bdermanmd @VPrasadMDMPH @VincentRK @myelomaMD @Geoff_Uy For main heme malignancies i go through the clinical results categories for oral abstracts and read ones that stand out/may alter practice.

For clinical interests (t cell/skin lymphoma, histiocytosis) I review all oral abstracts (usually not many).

Leave it to Twitter for rest!

@LeonidasPlatan1 @BrownHospMed A teaching point.  Per WHO 2022 "hairy cell leukemia variant" no longer exists.  

It is now known as "splenic B-cell lymphoma/leukemia with prominent nucleoli"!

@sanamloghavi https://t.co/gala98hYjA

@lechatnoir_89 @MartinTallman We have a front line trial using ino followed by blina

Off trial I had been using the GRALL SA01 with quick pivot to blina after some chemo.

T-ALL in the elderly is hard.  IF they can tolerate it I still use hyperCVAD with lower dose AraC and lots of supportive care

